1
00:00:17,708 --> 00:00:19,208
In Norse mythology, legend has
it that souls of the people

2
00:00:19,291 --> 00:00:21,083
who die in battle
will go to Valhalla,

3
00:00:21,166 --> 00:00:22,208
which is an honorable place

4
00:00:22,291 --> 00:00:23,875
where they can
hang out with Thor.

5
00:00:23,958 --> 00:00:25,583
Even if I die in battle today,

6
00:00:25,666 --> 00:00:27,666
I'll come back to life
tomorrow and die again!

7
00:00:27,750 --> 00:00:30,500
I'm personally torn on whether
Valhalla is heaven or hell

8
00:00:30,583 --> 00:00:33,958
because I'm not clear on
their sauna availability.

9
00:00:34,041 --> 00:00:35,708
Oh, wow. Was that a laugh?

10
00:00:35,791 --> 00:00:37,333
Gnarly!

11
00:00:37,416 --> 00:00:39,750
If I were still young, I would
have been down to go. Fo sho!

12
00:00:39,833 --> 00:00:41,833
Oh, I don't know about that.

13
00:00:41,916 --> 00:00:43,333
[FINLAND gasps]
What are you talking about?

14
00:00:43,416 --> 00:00:44,583
You're not that old!

15
00:00:59,625 --> 00:01:03,708
[NARRATOR] In 1657, Denmark
and Sweden started a war.

16
00:01:03,791 --> 00:01:04,875
Another war.

17
00:01:04,958 --> 00:01:07,541
I'm not sure which one--
They fought a lot.

18
00:01:07,625 --> 00:01:09,791
While Sweden was away
deluging Poland,

19
00:01:09,875 --> 00:01:12,958
Denmark used the opportunity
to attack Sweden's house.

20
00:01:13,041 --> 00:01:14,875
Being no match for
Denmark's fleet,

21
00:01:14,958 --> 00:01:17,250
and since the ocean wasn't
really his thing anyway,

22
00:01:17,333 --> 00:01:20,166
Sweden had to get back by
land... through Germany!

23
00:01:20,250 --> 00:01:21,375
Probably sober.

24
00:01:24,708 --> 00:01:26,625
[DENMARK]
Look at that, broskinke,

25
00:01:26,708 --> 00:01:29,583
the ocean is frozen as
far as the eye can see!

26
00:01:29,666 --> 00:01:33,125
Excited about the snow and
ice? What are you, a dog?

27
00:01:33,208 --> 00:01:35,125
This is a once in a
century cold wave!

28
00:01:35,208 --> 00:01:36,583
We're talking about history and

29
00:01:36,666 --> 00:01:38,833
that my nipples are about
to freeze off. It's amazing!

30
00:01:38,916 --> 00:01:41,583
Well, don't be surprised if
the cold gives you a cold.

31
00:01:41,666 --> 00:01:44,041
Come on, let's get back to
the station and do the chess.

32
00:01:44,125 --> 00:01:45,250
I'll win this time!

33
00:01:45,333 --> 00:01:47,125
We're in the middle
of a war, Denmark.

34
00:01:47,208 --> 00:01:49,000
Can we afford to
play games like that?

35
00:01:49,083 --> 00:01:50,583
You're such a worrier!

36
00:01:50,666 --> 00:01:54,333
No one would bother to attack
us on such a freezing cold day!

37
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:56,000
You might wanna look out there.

38
00:01:56,083 --> 00:01:57,291
[DENMARK]
Uh?

39
00:01:57,375 --> 00:01:59,416
Whoa! Something just
moved out on the ice.

40
00:01:59,500 --> 00:02:01,041
What kind of animal
could that be?

41
00:02:01,125 --> 00:02:02,083
[gasps]

42
00:02:03,708 --> 00:02:07,666
[SWEDEN growls]

43
00:02:07,750 --> 00:02:08,958
[DENMARK]
Damn!

44
00:02:09,041 --> 00:02:11,541
He walked over the frozen
ocean to attack us?

45
00:02:12,625 --> 00:02:14,291
Got any ideas?

46
00:02:14,375 --> 00:02:16,625
Don't worry. I've got this
thing in the bag, baby!

47
00:02:16,708 --> 00:02:18,458
TCB is what being
a Dane is about!

48
00:02:18,541 --> 00:02:21,166
Our motto is to kick ass
and take names, after all!

49
00:02:21,250 --> 00:02:23,250
But what will we do?
We're defenseless,

50
00:02:23,333 --> 00:02:25,250
and the only reason they
came here is to fight.

51
00:02:25,333 --> 00:02:26,875
Seems kinda hopeless.

52
00:02:26,958 --> 00:02:29,958
Leaders always know what to say,
and I'm no exception, homes.

53
00:02:31,750 --> 00:02:33,500
Watch and learn, little brother.

54
00:02:36,041 --> 00:02:38,125
Not bad, Sver-eh, not bad.

55
00:02:38,208 --> 00:02:39,583
You may defeat me here,

56
00:02:39,666 --> 00:02:41,333
but my second and third
selves will surely--

57
00:02:41,416 --> 00:02:43,166
--[thud]
--[DENMARK groaning]

58
00:02:43,250 --> 00:02:44,875
[DENMARK] Are you
watching, little brother?

59
00:02:44,958 --> 00:02:47,375
This is how a great
leader should fall!

60
00:02:47,458 --> 00:02:49,666
Oh man, did I just break a nail?

61
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:54,750
Since we've been fighting wars
lately, expenses have been high,

62
00:02:54,833 --> 00:02:56,625
so can you ask
Norway if it's cool

63
00:02:56,708 --> 00:02:58,458
to increase their
taxes, as well?

64
00:02:58,541 --> 00:03:00,666
[DENMARK]
I can't exactly refuse my boss.

65
00:03:00,750 --> 00:03:03,583
So I went to Nor's house for
the first time in a while.

66
00:03:03,666 --> 00:03:05,958
And whoa did it look ghetto.

67
00:03:06,041 --> 00:03:07,583
[DANISH OFFICIAL]
How could anyone live in that?

68
00:03:07,666 --> 00:03:09,333
Maybe he moved or something.

69
00:03:11,333 --> 00:03:13,833
You don't have to act
like my place is in ruins.

70
00:03:13,916 --> 00:03:15,375
I came to hang out with you!

71
00:03:15,458 --> 00:03:16,416
[DANISH OFFICIAL]
Ahem.

72
00:03:16,500 --> 00:03:18,208
Hang out with you
and talk to you

73
00:03:18,291 --> 00:03:20,166
about something you may
think is important!

74
00:03:20,250 --> 00:03:22,791
[NORWAY] You could at least
act like you feel guilty.

75
00:03:22,875 --> 00:03:23,958
Come in.

76
00:03:27,708 --> 00:03:30,625
Yo, don't you think your house
is a little too old, now?

77
00:03:30,708 --> 00:03:32,625
I mean, how can you
live in this dump?

78
00:03:32,708 --> 00:03:34,916
I can just send you a new
one if you want me to.

79
00:03:35,000 --> 00:03:36,458
Don't be so idiotic.

80
00:03:36,541 --> 00:03:39,291
There are other things
that are a higher priority.

81
00:03:39,375 --> 00:03:41,458
I shouldn't have to be
the one to remind you that

82
00:03:41,541 --> 00:03:44,000
we have been getting attacked
far too much lately.

83
00:03:44,083 --> 00:03:45,916
And besides, you've
been doing your best,

84
00:03:46,000 --> 00:03:48,375
and that makes me
grateful to live here.

85
00:03:48,458 --> 00:03:51,791
Norway... You didn't have to
endure this all by yourself

86
00:03:51,875 --> 00:03:53,041
without saying anything!

87
00:03:53,125 --> 00:03:54,708
I didn't realize you'd go so far

88
00:03:54,791 --> 00:03:56,083
--to be considerate.
--You're too loud.

89
00:03:56,166 --> 00:03:57,833
Will you get to
the point, please?

90
00:03:57,916 --> 00:03:58,666
[NORWAY]
Right.

91
00:03:58,750 --> 00:04:00,291
Now, what brought you here?

92
00:04:00,375 --> 00:04:02,125
We're gonna be best
friends forever!

93
00:04:02,208 --> 00:04:03,583
--I swear it!
--[NORWAY] You're too loud.

94
00:04:03,666 --> 00:04:05,458
--No one can separate us!
--Why don't we just go home?

95
00:04:05,541 --> 00:04:07,708
Are you saying you went there
and came all the way back

96
00:04:07,791 --> 00:04:09,708
without mentioning the
word "tax" to him?

97
00:04:09,791 --> 00:04:11,875
Might wanna keep things
as they are for now.

98
00:04:11,958 --> 00:04:14,000
My best friend is the
most amazing person

99
00:04:14,083 --> 00:04:16,291
on the whole globe, and
I've been making him suffer

100
00:04:16,375 --> 00:04:17,875
and I didn't know.
I didn't know at all!

101
00:04:17,958 --> 00:04:19,791
[NARRATOR]
And so, unyielding guilt

102
00:04:19,875 --> 00:04:22,541
helped Denmark finally be
as considerate as Norway,

103
00:04:22,625 --> 00:04:25,875
whose tax increases were put
on hold for quite a long time.

104
00:04:25,958 --> 00:04:28,333
[DENMARK crying]

105
00:04:28,416 --> 00:04:31,541
I'll be stronger.
I'll be stronger for you!

